                ],
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "Herb Lerner (1915-1972) was a Jewish Communist born in Lithuania, a soldier stationed during World War II in North Africa and Italy, and later the New Jersey director of the International Union of Mine, Mill, and Smelter Workers."
                    }
